title: Coaches' Corner: UMD Football's Greg Bower
text:
Coaches' Corner: UMD Football's Greg Bower 
By Zach Schneider October 8, 2015 Updated Oct 8, 2015 at 8:52 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) football team is (3-2) this season after a dominative 47-14 road win over MSU-Moorhead, which was the main topic of discussion in this week's "Coaches' Corner" with special teams coordinator Greg Bower. 
This conversation is part of the weekly show "Bulldog Country," which covers all things UMD and airs every Friday night at 6:30 p.m. on the My 9 Sports Network.
